to throw us a whole party.

00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:23.398 position:50% align:center line:84%
It honestly makes
me feel kinda weird.

00:00:23.481 --> 00:00:25.275 position:50% align:center line:84%
Hold on. Are you nervous?

00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:28.486 position:50% align:center line:84%
Uh! No. I'm just new
to this group stuff.

00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:30.321 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIORIKO] Thank you for
the warm reception.

00:00:30.405 --> 00:00:31.948 position:50% align:center line:84%
We still have much to learn,

00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:34.743 position:50% align:center line:84%
but we look forward to
working alongside you.

00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:37.537 position:50% align:center line:84%
Why are you talking like you're
giving some formal speech?

00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:40.165 position:50% align:center line:84%
Aw, Mia-chi, you must feel
like you've always been

00:00:40.248 --> 00:00:41.791 position:50% align:center line:84%
in the club if you're
so comfortable.

00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.793 position:50% align:center line:84%
[MIA]
I told you not to call me that!

00:00:43.877 --> 00:00:46.087 position:50% align:center line:84%
Our future looks
livelier than ever.

00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:48.214 position:50% align:center line:84%
If we recruit any more
idols the club room's

00:00:48.298 --> 00:00:50.258 position:50% align:center line:84%
gonna start to
feel kinda cramped.

00:00:50.342 --> 00:00:51.801 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIORIKO]
I'd like to submit my official

00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:53.887 position:50% align:center line:84%
membership application,
President.

00:00:53.970 --> 00:00:56.848 position:50% align:center line:84%
Sorry, but I'm not
the idol club president.

00:00:56.931 --> 00:00:58.600 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIORIKO]
Oh, I beg your pardon.

00:00:58.683 --> 00:01:00.810 position:50% align:center line:84%
Yu. You'll find everything
is in order.

00:01:00.894 --> 00:01:03.063 position:50% align:center line:84%
Nope. I'm not the one
running things, either.

00:01:03.146 --> 00:01:05.315 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Ahem!

00:01:05.398 --> 00:01:07.650 position:50% align:center line:84%
The president of this
school idol club is not only

00:01:07.734 --> 00:01:10.862 position:50% align:center line:84%
the most popular and most
talented person in the room.

00:01:10.945 --> 00:01:14.240 position:50% align:center line:84%
She's also the cutest by far!

00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:15.617 position:50% align:center line:84%
What? I'm in charge?

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:17.410 position:50% align:center line:84%
No, of course not.

00:01:17.494 --> 00:01:19.287 position:50% align:center line:84%
So, who? I'd say you're all

00:01:19.371 --> 00:01:21.164 position:50% align:center line:84%
rather popular,
talented, and cute.

00:01:21.247 --> 00:01:23.917 position:50% align:center line:84%
Kasukasu's the performer
staging this show.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.794 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Do not call me that!

00:01:25.877 --> 00:01:28.338 position:50% align:center line:84%
New decree!
As president of this club,

00:01:28.421 --> 00:01:30.340 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm banning
unapproved nicknames.

00:01:30.423 --> 00:01:33.259 position:50% align:center line:84%
You sound like a puppy.
So yappy.

00:01:33.343 --> 00:01:34.928 position:50% align:center line:84%
A puppy?

00:01:35.011 --> 00:01:37.514 position:50% align:center line:84%
You take that back
right now, ya newbie!

00:01:37.597 --> 00:01:39.015 position:50% align:center line:84%
[growls]

00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:40.558 position:50% align:center line:84%
Now, now, Kasumi.

00:01:40.642 --> 00:01:43.103 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI] This club desperately
needs to learn some respect!

00:01:43.186 --> 00:01:45.689 position:50% align:center line:84%
Wait, a sec.

00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:49.818 position:50% align:center line:84%
Hey. Your place is giant, right
Shizuko? Let's sleep over!

00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:53.029 position:50% align:center line:84%
Uh? Yes. Of course.
That sounds nice.

00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:55.031 position:50% align:center line:84%
Girls. Listen up!

00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:56.491 position:50% align:center line:84%
Since we've got some time off,

00:01:56.574 --> 00:01:59.244 position:50% align:center line:84%
we'll have a slumber party
so we get even closer.

00:01:59.327 --> 00:02:01.579 position:50% align:center line:84%
Strong bonds make
for strong idols.

00:02:01.663 --> 00:02:02.997 position:50% align:center line:84%
A sleepover?

00:02:03.081 --> 00:02:05.417 position:50% align:center line:84%
Oh, yes. My kinda party.

00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:08.420 position:50% align:center line:84%
During the day we could
explore the town together.

00:02:08.503 --> 00:02:10.547 position:50% align:center line:84%
How exciting.

00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:13.425 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI] He, he, he.
This slumber party will be

00:02:13.508 --> 00:02:16.511 position:50% align:center line:84%
the perfect way for me to
remind everybody that no one

00:02:16.594 --> 00:02:18.930 position:50% align:center line:84%
would be a better
president than me.

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:58.071 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI] "Kasumin's Plan to
Prove She's the President."

00:03:58.154 --> 00:04:00.115 position:50% align:center line:84%
My grand scheme
to garner respect

00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:01.866 position:50% align:center line:84%
and adoration from
the girls and become

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center line:84%
the one true leader
starts right now.

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:06.121 position:50% align:center line:84%
This is amazing!

00:04:06.204 --> 00:04:09.290 position:50% align:center line:84%
Kasumi planned out
every detail of the day!

00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:11.751 position:50% align:center line:84%
This must've taken forever.

00:04:11.835 --> 00:04:14.254 position:50% align:center line:84%
Well, a good leader
is prepared.

00:04:14.337 --> 00:04:15.839 position:50% align:center line:84%
Let's see here.

00:04:15.922 --> 00:04:19.134 position:50% align:center line:84%
First off is a shopping trip to
get us energized and talking.

00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.468 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Or so you think.

00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:22.470 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm actually going to play
the knowledgeable guide

00:04:22.554 --> 00:04:24.222 position:50% align:center line:84%
and show off my
leadership skills

00:04:24.305 --> 00:04:27.559 position:50% align:center line:84%
as we stroll from
store to store!

00:04:27.642 --> 00:04:30.437 position:50% align:center line:84%
[LANZHU speaking Chinese]
What a lovely place.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.439 position:50% align:center line:84%
Less talk n' more browsing!

00:04:32.522 --> 00:04:35.108 position:50% align:center line:84%
We're supposed to go
as a group! Hey, wait!

00:04:35.191 --> 00:04:37.610 position:50% align:center line:84%
Oh. I see a shop
you would like!

00:04:37.694 --> 00:04:39.487 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI whining]
We shouldn't be separated!

00:04:39.571 --> 00:04:41.448 position:50% align:center line:84%
This is for me?

00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:44.367 position:50% align:center line:84%
Keep it close to you.
Wear it all day.

00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:46.119 position:50% align:center line:84%
What a cute little kitty cat.

00:04:46.202 --> 00:04:49.414 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN laughs]
It's lovely. Thank you.

00:04:49.497 --> 00:04:51.374 position:50% align:center line:84%
Dangit! I was supposed
to take the lead

00:04:51.458 --> 00:04:52.876 position:50% align:center line:84%
and show everybody how good I am

00:04:52.959 --> 00:04:55.003 position:50% align:center line:84%
at being in charge
of the afternoon!

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.588 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AYUMU]
Look at this hat.

00:04:56.671 --> 00:04:59.549 position:50% align:center line:84%
Adorable, right?
What do you think?

00:04:59.632 --> 00:05:02.135 position:50% align:center line:84%
[gasps] It would look
great on me!

00:05:02.218 --> 00:05:03.511 position:50% align:center line:84%
[BOTH laughing]

00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:04.721 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AI]
I could rock that.

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:06.306 position:50% align:center line:84%
--[MIA] This is pretty.
--[YU] Can't resist.

00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:07.515 position:50% align:center line:84%
--[LANZHU] Maybe a small bag.
--[SHIZUKU] How can I choose?

00:05:07.599 --> 00:05:09.934 position:50% align:center line:84%
--[RINA] I want this.
--[KANATA] Precious.

00:05:10.018 --> 00:05:10.852 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN laughs]

00:05:10.935 --> 00:05:13.021 position:50% align:center line:84%
[MIA]
Karin.

00:05:13.104 --> 00:05:15.607 position:50% align:center line:84%
Where are we supposed
to regroup again?

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:17.067 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN]
Uh?

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:19.194 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SETSUNA laughs]

00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:20.820 position:50% align:center line:84%
Looks yummy!

00:05:20.904 --> 00:05:22.280 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SETSUNA, EMMA]
Ah!

00:05:24.074 --> 00:05:26.284 position:50% align:center line:84%
--[EMMA] Buono!
--[SETSUNA] Delicious!

00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:28.161 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AYUMU]
Strange.

00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:30.663 position:50% align:center line:84%
Has anyone seen
Mia and Karin lately?

00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:33.833 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KANATA] Oh, yeah, I saw them
walking together earlier.

00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:35.585 position:50% align:center line:84%
We were supposed to
meet up right now.

00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:37.295 position:50% align:center line:84%
I wonder where they ran off to.

00:05:37.379 --> 00:05:39.255 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Have no fear!

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:42.717 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm on it! Leave this case
to President Kasumin!

00:05:42.801 --> 00:05:46.554 position:50% align:center line:84%
I have a pretty good idea where
our missing members ran off to.

00:05:46.638 --> 00:05:48.098 position:50% align:center line:84%
[GROUP]
Huh?

00:05:48.181 --> 00:05:50.100 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI] I'm positive the two
of them are still together.

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.644 position:50% align:center line:84%
Karin has absolutely
no sense of direction,

00:05:52.727 --> 00:05:54.187 position:50% align:center line:84%
so there's an extremely
high chance

00:05:54.270 --> 00:05:56.189 position:50% align:center line:84%
she doesn't know
where she's going.

00:05:56.272 --> 00:06:00.610 position:50% align:center line:84%
Which would mean they're heading
to a place Miako wants to go.

00:06:00.694 --> 00:06:02.570 position:50% align:center line:84%
They're chowing
down on burgers.

00:06:02.654 --> 00:06:06.199 position:50% align:center line:84%
Or they're possibly
in Chinatown.

00:06:06.282 --> 00:06:08.368 position:50% align:center line:84%
[EMMA]
We've got this covered.

00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:10.453 position:50% align:center line:84%
Emma knew that this
would happen.

00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:13.707 position:50% align:center line:84%
She asked me to come up
with a way to track Karin.

00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:16.418 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
What?

00:06:16.501 --> 00:06:17.752 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN]
On second thought,

00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:20.088 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm not sure this is where
we're supposed to be.

00:06:20.171 --> 00:06:22.298 position:50% align:center line:84%
Wow! A baseball stadium!

00:06:22.382 --> 00:06:24.426 position:50% align:center line:84%
You brought me
to the best place!

00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:25.635 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN]
Uh?

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:31.224 position:50% align:center line:84%
Ya hear that? The staccato
crack of ball meeting bat.

00:06:31.307 --> 00:06:33.560 position:50% align:center line:84%
The crowd is cheering as
they watch the players

00:06:33.643 --> 00:06:36.604 position:50% align:center line:84%
round the bases,
dashing towards home plate!

00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:40.859 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN] Mm... No, I don't
think there's a game.

00:06:40.942 --> 00:06:43.194 position:50% align:center line:84%
It's the love of the
sport echoing through

00:06:43.278 --> 00:06:46.573 position:50% align:center line:84%
the stadium walls.
Can't you feel it?

00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:48.450 position:50% align:center line:84%
I didn't peg you for a fan.

00:06:48.533 --> 00:06:51.870 position:50% align:center line:84%
And I didn't peg you for
someone who gets lost easily.

00:06:51.953 --> 00:06:53.163 position:50% align:center line:84%
[EMMA]
There you are!

00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:57.292 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KARIN] Mm? Emma.
I'm surprised you found us.

00:06:58.543 --> 00:07:00.420 position:50% align:center line:84%
[RINA]
Leave it to me.

00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:04.549 position:50% align:center line:84%
[YU] Next, it says we're
supposed to improve comradery

00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:06.426 position:50% align:center line:84%
through group sports.

00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:07.802 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Or so you believe.

00:07:07.886 --> 00:07:10.430 position:50% align:center line:84%
This is where my
captainliness will shine.

00:07:10.513 --> 00:07:11.890 position:50% align:center line:84%
[whistle blows]

00:07:11.973 --> 00:07:14.517 position:50% align:center line:84%
Okay! Let's get
this game started!

00:07:14.601 --> 00:07:16.186 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SETSUNA]
Aren't you exuberant?

00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:17.562 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Take that!

00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:19.022 position:50% align:center line:84%
[gasps] There!

00:07:19.105 --> 00:07:20.523 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SETSUNA grunting]

00:07:22.108 --> 00:07:24.235 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIZUKU] I am the ace
of the volleyball team!

00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:26.988 position:50% align:center line:84%
Okay, I'm actually terrible,
but as long as I fully inhabit

00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:30.116 position:50% align:center line:84%
the role, I can return
any pass! Probably!

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:31.743 position:50% align:center line:84%
Ack!

00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:37.040 position:50% align:center line:84%
Thanks for the setup.
Here I go!

00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:39.834 position:50% align:center line:84%
Mine! [yelps]

00:07:39.918 --> 00:07:41.419 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AI]
Way to use your head!

00:07:41.503 --> 00:07:43.838 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm gonna show these
girls real skills.

00:07:43.922 --> 00:07:46.591 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KANATA]
Gotta wait your turn.

00:07:46.675 --> 00:07:49.469 position:50% align:center line:84%
The time will pass faster
if you take a snooze.

00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:51.513 position:50% align:center line:84%
Wha-- Kanata?

00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:53.348 position:50% align:center line:84%
You're comfy.

00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:57.852 position:50% align:center line:84%
Next topic is veggies.

00:07:57.936 --> 00:08:01.690 position:50% align:center line:84%
That's easy. This beet
takes me back to my roots.

00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:05.235 position:50% align:center line:84%
[YU]
Beet! Like, you eat!

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.737 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AYUMU]
Okay. Now fish.

00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:11.282 position:50% align:center line:84%
Darn. I haven't found
the right time yet.

00:08:11.366 --> 00:08:13.284 position:50% align:center line:84%
[AYUMU]
How 'bout, cooking?

00:08:13.368 --> 00:08:15.370 position:50% align:center line:84%
Oh, did you want to
bring something up?

00:08:15.453 --> 00:08:16.830 position:50% align:center line:84%
Oh, it's nothing. Really.

00:08:16.913 --> 00:08:19.249 position:50% align:center line:84%
[YU giggles]
Stop. I can't breathe.

00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:22.043 position:50% align:center line:84%
This isn't over yet.

00:08:22.127 --> 00:08:27.257 position:50% align:center line:84%
My plan to prove I'm the best
prez has only just begun.

00:08:28.341 --> 00:08:31.386 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIZUKU] We'll have to
take a bus from here.

00:08:31.469 --> 00:08:35.724 position:50% align:center line:84%
[GROU gasps]
Your house is huge!

00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:37.100 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIORIKO grunts]

00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:39.227 position:50% align:center line:84%
What's the matter, Shioriko?

00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:40.812 position:50% align:center line:84%
The thing is...

00:08:40.895 --> 00:08:43.565 position:50% align:center line:84%
This is going to be my
very first slumber party.

00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:45.734 position:50% align:center line:84%
So I'm a little nervous.

00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:47.902 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm in the same boat.

00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:51.990 position:50% align:center line:84%
O-ho, then I hope the two of you
followed proper protocol.

00:08:52.073 --> 00:08:54.075 position:50% align:center line:84%
Like, you brought
your own pillows, right?

00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:55.827 position:50% align:center line:84%
It'll be weird if you didn't.

00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:56.995 position:50% align:center line:84%
Our pillows?

00:08:57.078 --> 00:08:59.456 position:50% align:center line:84%
I'm afraid I wasn't
aware of that rule.

00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:01.207 position:50% align:center line:84%
She's messing with you.

00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:02.834 position:50% align:center line:84%
[KASUMI]
Heh!

00:09:02.917 --> 00:09:04.461 position:50% align:center line:84%
I always have one.

00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:06.212 position:50% align:center line:84%
Huh?

00:09:07.839 --> 00:09:09.799 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIZUKU]
Come on inside! Welcome!

00:09:09.883 --> 00:09:11.301 position:50% align:center line:84%
[barks]

00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:14.471 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIZUKU] Ophelia! Did you come
outside just to greet us?

00:09:14.554 --> 00:09:16.014 position:50% align:center line:84%
[barks]

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:18.850 position:50% align:center line:84%
[SHIZUKU'S MOTHER]
This is such a pleasure.

00:09:18.933 --> 00:09:20.685 position:50% align:center line:84%
Make yourselves
at home my dears.

00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:22.812 position:50% align:center line:84%
We're awfully grateful.

00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:27.233 position:50% align:center line:84%
[GROUP gasping]

00:09:27.317 --> 00:09:30.362 position:50% align:center line:84%
[GROUP]
Thank you for the food!

00:09:30.445 --> 00:09:32.947 position:50% align:center line:84%
[EMMA]
It looks so good!

00:09:34.824 --> 00:09:35.909 position:50% align:center line:84%
--[SHIORIKO] Now roll it.
--[MIA] Like this?

00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:38.620 position:50% align:center line:84%
[LANZHU speaking Chinese]

00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:40.163 position:50% align:center line:84%
